    "faq_with_image_m73Xra": {
      "type": "faq-with-image",
      "blocks": {
        "accordion_GhRGXt": {
          "type": "accordion",
          "settings": {
            "accordion_header": "How do I select the perfect chain length and style for my personal neckwear aesthetic?",
            "open_by_default": false,
            "text": "<p>The ideal necklace or pendant should harmonise flawlessly with your individual silhouette and the intended occasion. Understanding proper scale is key to sophisticated jewellery design; a master goldsmith helps you discern if a shorter, choker-style piece best complements your décolletage, or if an extended, elegant link chain draws attention downwards. </p><p>While we can offer initial guidance remotely, we strongly recommend an appointment at our Chichester Showroom. Our team there can measure and advise on the optimal length of chains, ensuring your new creation—whether a delicate pendant or a bold collar piece—is perfectly proportioned for you, regardless of which local community in {{ block.settings.page.metafields.custom.location.value }}inspires you.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "accordion_HmVJLJ": {
          "type": "accordion",
          "settings": {
            "accordion_header": "If I want to commission a bespoke necklace based on sentimental symbolism (e.g., family emblems), where should I start?",
            "open_by_default": false,
            "text": "<p>A commissioned necklace is perhaps the most deeply personal form of wearable art. The process begins with sharing your unique story and symbolic intentions—from remembering a loved one via a miniature locket pendant to representing a family emblem through an engraved plaque. </p><p>For this level of delicate storytelling, engaging with our master goldsmiths in person at the Chichester Showroom is invaluable. </p><p>Viewing samples, discussing the weight of different metallic settings, and handling the design materials allows us to transform your memory into a tangible, ethically sourced piece; we even offer private consultations for those located near {{ block.settings.page.metafields.custom.location.value }}.<br/><br/></p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "accordion_xFhTbU": {
          "type": "accordion",
          "settings": {
            "accordion_header": "Do you work with antique or vintage pendant elements for remodelling into modern necklaces?",
            "open_by_default": false,
            "text": "<p>We specialise in revitalising jewellery with rich history. When adapting a vintage pendant—perhaps one passed down through generations—into a completely renewed, contemporary necklace, meticulous care is required to honour its provenance while updating its aesthetic appeal. Our skilled artisans treat these pieces as historical commissions. </p><p>All specialised repair and remodelling are conducted within the security of our on-site Chichester workshop, guaranteeing that your heirloom never leaves our protective local domain. </p><p>We encourage an appointment at the Showroom to assess these precious family pieces from {{ block.settings.page.metafields.custom.location.value }}.<br/><br/></p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "accordion_pxHnfz": {
          "type": "accordion",
          "settings": {
            "accordion_header": "What is the difference between a classic pendant setting and a modern, architectural piece?",
            "open_by_default": false,
            "text": "<p>The distinction lies in the artistic intention—a classical piece prioritises the emotional connection with the central gemstone, while a modern, architectural design often treats the metal itself as a form of art. </p><p>Our latest creations showcase both; some delicate pendants feature meticulously set gemstones (with strong attention to GIA-certified quality), while others boast bold, forged geometric shapes in Platinum or Gold. </p><p>Understanding this contrast is best done by seeing and holding the pieces during an appointment at our Chichester Showroom, letting us guide you towards your preferred style of enduring glamour.<br/><br/></p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "accordion_BRezAN": {
          "type": "accordion",
          "settings": {
            "accordion_header": "How do I ensure the metal backing (chain) for my necklace matches the pendant's quality and longevity?",
            "open_by_default": false,
            "text": "<p>The chain is the supporting structure that must complement, not compete with, the principal design element. When commissioning a piece, we evaluate the intrinsic properties of both elements—from matching the alloy weight to ensuring both undergo the same high-quality finishing in our local workshop. </p><p>Whether you are securing yourself a piece before travelling from {{ block.settings.page.metafields.custom.location.value }} or building an entirely new ensemble, all materials are selected for their enduring strength and ethical integrity, guaranteeing that your stunning confluence of pendant and chain is built to last for generations.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "accordion_GhRGXt",
